A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Joyce Carter Stevens; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Joyce Carter Stevens has long been recognized by the citizens of this state for
3 the vital role that she has played in leadership and her deep personal commitment to the
4 welfare of the citizens of Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, Joyce was raised in Adel, Georgia, and served as Vice-President of Sales and
6 Marketing at Del-Cook Lumber Company from 1964 to 1981; and
7 WHEREAS, her first major involvement with the Republican Party was in fundraising for
8 Mack Mattingly's 1980 United States Senate race, which led to her organizing the Cook
9 County Republican Party and becoming involved with the highest members of the party; and
10 WHEREAS, she was selected to serve as Executive Director of the Georgia Republican Party
11 from 1981 to 1983, during which time her main focus was on growing the party's fundraising
12 budget; and
13 WHEREAS, she made history as the first female candidate on the general election ballot in
14 Georgia when she ran for a position on the Public Service Commission in 1984; and
